            "type": "text",
            "text": "ACE-Step 1.5 Turbo vs openai: Core Technical Differences"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ACE-Step 1.5 Turbo is optimized for low-latency inference with a transformer-based architecture, supporting up to 8K context windows. In contrast, OpenAI models like GPT-4 offer broader multimodal capabilities but may introduce higher latency in high-throughput scenarios. Key distinctions include tokenization efficiency—ACE-Step uses a custom tokenizer reducing overhead by 15%—and API design, where ACE-Step emphasizes RESTful endpoints with WebSocket support for streaming, while OpenAI relies on similar REST APIs but with different rate limit structures."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "API Endpoints and Authentication Protocols"
